<br>
<b>Ingredients</b>
<br><div class="mobileAdPlacement"></div>
<ul><li> 1 lb. lean ground beef </li><li> 1 medium onion, finely chopped</li><li>1 clove garlic, crushed</li><li>3 slices bacon, cut into small pieces</li><li>1 – 28oz. can diced tomatoes</li><li>½ cup red wine</li><li>1 tsp. dried oregano</li><li>1 tsp. salt</li><li>1 cup diced potatoes</li><li>1 lb. dried split green peas</li><li>8 cups chicken or vegetable stock, or water</li></ul><br>
<b>Preparation time:</b> 10 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Cook time:</b> 1hour 30 minutes<br><br>
<b>Steps:</b>
<br><div class="teadsAdPlacement"></div>
1. Place the beef in a non-stick pan and gently heat, stirring and breaking up the mixture. Cook until no longer pink. Drain any excess fat from the pan. <br>
2. Add the onion, garlic and bacon, and increase the heat to fry the ingredients gently. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes stirring frequently, or until the onion is softened.<br>
3. Add the diced tomatoes to the pan along with the red wine, oregano and salt. Bring to a boil, stir and reduce the heat. Cover and leave to simmer gently for 35 minutes to 40 minutes, stirring frequently. The alcohol in the wine will cook off as it simmers. 
